entries.title: Qatar Warns Brussels Bribery Allegations Could Hurt Energy Talks With Europe
entries.description: The Persian Gulf kingdom is one of Europe’s best hopes for weaning itself off Russian natural gas.

entries.title: Battle for Bakhmut Is Critical Test of Russia's Prospects in Ukraine
entries.description: Russia’s new war commander promised advances in exchange for a retreat in the south. This eastern city is where he is trying to show those gains.

entries.title: Israel Deports Palestinian-French Lawyer Despite Condemnations
entries.description: Paris and human-rights groups said sending Jerusalem-born Salah Hammouri to France violates international law.

entries.title: Tunisian Opposition Urges President to Step Down After Low Voter Turnout
entries.description: Fewer than 9% of eligible voters cast ballots in parliamentary elections this weekend.

entries.title: Putin's Belarus Visit Stokes Fears It Could Be Drawn Into Ukraine War
entries.description: Russia’s closest ally has resisted being pulled into the conflict, but pressure from Moscow to open a new front appears to be growing.

entries.title: Pope Francis Says He Has Written Resignation Letter in Case of Incapacity
entries.description: The pontiff, who has used a wheelchair since May, turned 86 on Saturday.

entries.title: Time Might Run Out for Japan's Low-Rate Policy
entries.description: The weak yen and rising inflation are putting pressure on the central bank to raise rates, but doing so could send interest costs on the government’s massive debt soaring.

entries.title: Rockets Kill One in Russian Region Near Ukraine
entries.description: The salvo was intercepted, but debris and shrapnel fell on Belgorod, the region’s governor said.

entries.title: Dogs Pay the Price in Italian Truffle War
entries.description: The delicacy has never been more lucrative for hunters, fueling a rivalry that sometimes turns deadly for their specially trained hounds.

entries.title: North Korea Launches Two Missiles, Adding to a Historic Year of Weapons Testing
entries.description: The Kim Jong Un regime has conducted more than 30 rounds of weapons tests in 2022—more than it has ever done in a single year by a wide margin.
